This issue is for tracking the development of the ETL process that was copied from the `able-workflow-etl-copier` template.

This checklist is for a project developer implementing the generated ETL scaffold in a project repository. Workflow runners should usually leave committed config files alone and use `config/config.local.yaml` or parent-workflow config overrides instead.

- [ ] Copy-paste these contents into a new github issue for the ETL process
- [ ] In the github issue, create a new branch to work on the issue
- [ ] Fetch and checkout that branch in your local development environment.
- [ ] Commit the changes made by the Copier template to the branch.
